<div><div><h2>L&T Q2 profit rises 23% to Rs2,230 crore, beats estimate</h2></div><div>industrial conglomerate larsen & toubro ltd posted a 22.6% jump in sept-quarter net profit underpinned by higher order intake. net profit came in at rs2230 crore ($301.64 million) in the second quarter compared with rs1820 crore a year earlier company said on wednesday. analysts on average had expected the mumbai-headquartered company to post a net profit of rs1719 crore according to refinitiv eikon data. revenue from operations jumped 21.3% to rs32081 crore. l&t s order book stood at rs2.81 trillion as of 30 september of which the international order book constituted 22%. the company recorded a one-off gain of rs295 crore in the quarter. it had reported an exceptional item of rs137 crore in the same period last year.</div></div>